This is what it's all about. Koll Superglide Almighty with chambered walnut body, carved Oregon birdseye maple top with orange tint nitro finish, myrtle neck, rosewood fretboard with slanted pearl ovoid inlays, TK Smith SV-1 pickups.

Playability is always our number one priority, but we put a lot of thought into the overall aesthetic, the wood choices, and the smallest details of our instruments.

Fresh off the workbench, this new Koll is available now at @themusicemporium.

It’s Michael Bashkin! Today I had a nice though all too short visit with guitar maker @bashkin_guitars .  What we build is quite different but we share many of the same lutherie philosophies, reverence for tradition coupled with hunger for better ways of doing, and a constant quest for improvement and innovation. We’ve both been at it for at least three decades and it was interesting to see the similarities in our work flow and tooling. I’d bet if we traded shops for a week we’d each have no problems making what we make. Michael has a brilliant podcast where he interviews amazing luthiers. https://www.fretboardjournal.com/tag/luthier-on-luthier/ Check it out! Recently Michael with @stewmac_guitar put out a thorough account of how a high end acoustic guitar is made start to finish. It’s super cool, check it out https://youtu.be/Dj5RewW11uM thanks Michael for the invitation and hospitality. I hope to see you in Portland one day. You can use my shop!

NEW! We’re huge fans of the leather goods (and mind-blowing guitar skills) of Nevada-based artisan Matt Codina. We’ve been friends with Matt for years and we’re very proud of our first collaboration: a collection of handmade custom leather guitar straps.

The materials and build quality of these straps is incredible. Matt starts with Grade A Hermann Oak vegetable-tanned tooling leather from the oldest tannery in the US. This is one of the finest leathers in the world and will patina SOOOOOOO nicely. The shoulder pads are backed with shearling wool, and the straps feature solid brass roller buckles made in England. They’re available in black or natural, with either a smooth finish or a tooled Western design, and are adjustable Medium to Large length (45”-51”).

This is a limited batch (one dozen, only three straps of each color/style) so when they sell out we’ll take pre-orders for the next batch. They’re a perfect compliment to a Koll guitar, or any guitar for that matter!

Link in our bio to order.
